description: Powerfree kernel of cubefree part of n.
comments: If n=Product[Pj^Ej] then a(n)=Product[Pj^Fj], where Fj=0 if Ej is 0 or a multiple of 3 and Fj=1 otherwise.Multiplicative with a(p^e) = p^(if 3|e, then 0, else 1). - _Mitch Harris_, Apr 19 2005.
example: a(32)=2 because cubefree part of 32 is 4 and powerfree kernel of 4 is 2.
author: _Henry Bottomley_, Jun 25 2000
